<usermanual>
__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

									*The Reflective Functioning Questionnaire (RFQ)*
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 05-04-2018
last updated:  02-28-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-28-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements a computerized version of the Reflective Functioning Questionnaire (RFQ) by:

Fonagy P, Luyten P, Moulton-Perkins A, Lee YW, Warren F, Howard S, et al. 
Development and validation of a self-report measure of mentalizing: 
The Reflective Functioning Questionnaire. PLOS ONE. 2016;11(7):e0158678. 
doi: 10.1371/journal.pone.0158678

downloaded from: http://www.ucl.ac.uk/psychoanalysis/research/rfq

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
8 7-point Likert Scale, self-resport

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 1 minute to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'rfq8.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	 with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values 1-7, no rescoring/reversed scoring of raw data)
								see summary data file for rescored data
								
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'rfq8_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

RFQ_c:							Certainty about Mental States
								=> rescoring of q1, q2, q3, q4, q5, q6 responses into values.RFQ_c1-values.RFQ_c6
								with 1 = 3; 2 = 2; 3 = 1; 4+ = 0
								=> mean of the rescored RFQ_c values = RFQ_c
								
RFQ_u:							Uncertainty about Mental States 
								=> rescoring of q2, q4, q5, q6, q8 responses into values.RFQ_u2-values.RFQ_u8
								with 4 and below = 0, 5 = 1, 6 = 2, 7 = 3
								=> rescoring of q7 into values.RFQ_u with
								with 1 = 3; 2 = 2; 3 = 1; 4+ = 0
								=> mean of the rescored RFQ_u values => RFQ_u
							
+ original & rescored responses								
Example:
radiobuttons.q1.response:		original response
RFQc1:							rescored response (see above) 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
QUESTIONNAIRE SET-UP 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
8 7-point Likert Scale, self-resport

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
INSTRUCTIONS 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
see Editable Parameters
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code to 
further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage

</usermanual>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Please work through the next 8 statements. For each statement, select a response button between 1 and 7 to say how much you disagree or agree with the statement. Do not think too much about it – your initial responses are usually the best. Thank you.
"
</parameters>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.00%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>


<page end>
Thank you!
</page>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
							REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS:
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0

<defaults>
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, script.elapsedTime, 
script.completed, 
expressions.RFQ_c, expressions.RFQ_u,
radiobuttons.q1.response, values.RFQc1, 
radiobuttons.q2.response, values.RFQc2, values.RFQu2,
radiobuttons.q3.response, values.RFQc3,
radiobuttons.q4.response, values.RFQc4, values.RFQu4,
radiobuttons.q5.response, values.RFQc5, values.RFQu5,
radiobuttons.q6.response, values.RFQc6, values.RFQu6,
radiobuttons.q7.response, values.RFQu7,
radiobuttons.q8.response, values.RFQu8
)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/completed:				0 = script was not completed (script prematurely aborted); 1 = script was completed (all conditions run)

<values>
/RFQc1 = ""
/RFQc2 = ""
/RFQc3 = ""
/RFQc4 = ""
/RFQc5 = ""
/RFQc6 = ""

/RFQu2 = ""
/RFQu4 = ""
/RFQu5 = ""
/RFQu6 = ""
/RFQu7 = ""
/RFQu8 = ""
</values>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/recoding_RFQ_c = {
	if (radiobuttons.q1.response == 1){
		values.RFQc1 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q1.response == 2){
		values.RFQc1 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q1.response == 3){
		values.RFQc1 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q1.response >=4){
		values.RFQc1 = 0;
	}
	
	if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 1){
		values.RFQc2 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 2){
		values.RFQc2 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 3){
		values.RFQc2 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q2.response >=4){
		values.RFQc2 = 0;
	}	
	
	if (radiobuttons.q3.response == 1){
		values.RFQc3 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q3.response == 2){
		values.RFQc3 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q3.response == 3){
		values.RFQc3 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q3.response >=4){
		values.RFQc3 = 0;
	}

	if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 1){
		values.RFQc4 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 2){
		values.RFQc4 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 3){
		values.RFQc4 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q4.response >=4){
		values.RFQc4 = 0;
	}

	if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 1){
		values.RFQc5 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 2){
		values.RFQc5 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 3){
		values.RFQc5 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q5.response >=4){
		values.RFQc5 = 0;
	}	

	if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 1){
		values.RFQc6 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 2){
		values.RFQc6 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 3){
		values.RFQc6 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q6.response >=4){
		values.RFQc6 = 0;
	}			
}

/recoding_RFQ_u = {
	if (radiobuttons.q2.response < 5){
		values.RFQu2 = 0;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 5){
		values.RFQu2 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 6){
		values.RFQu2 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q2.response == 7){
		values.RFQu2 = 3;
	}	
	
	if (radiobuttons.q4.response < 5){
		values.RFQu4 = 0;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 5){
		values.RFQu4 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 6){
		values.RFQu4 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q4.response == 7){
		values.RFQu4 = 3;
	}	

	if (radiobuttons.q5.response < 5){
		values.RFQu5 = 0;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 5){
		values.RFQu5 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 6){
		values.RFQu5 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q5.response == 7){
		values.RFQu5 = 3;
	}

	if (radiobuttons.q6.response < 5){
		values.RFQu6 = 0;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 5){
		values.RFQu6 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 6){
		values.RFQu6 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q6.response == 7){
		values.RFQu6 = 3;
	}	

	if (radiobuttons.q7.response == 1){
		values.RFQu7 = 3;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q7.response == 2){
		values.RFQu7 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q7.response == 3){
		values.RFQu7 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q7.response > 3){
		values.RFQu7 = 0;
	}		
	
	if (radiobuttons.q8.response < 5){
		values.RFQu8 = 0;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q8.response == 5){
		values.RFQu8 = 1;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q8.response == 6){
		values.RFQu8 = 2;
	} else if (radiobuttons.q8.response == 7){
		values.RFQu8 = 3;
	}		
	
}

/RFQ_c = (values.RFQc1 + values.RFQc2 + values.RFQc3 + values.RFQc4 + values.RFQc5 + values.RFQc6)/6
/RFQ_u = (values.RFQu2 + values.RFQu4 + values.RFQu5 + values.RFQu6 + values.RFQu7 + values.RFQu8)/6
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1>
/caption = "People’s thoughts are a mystery to me"
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2>
/caption = "I don’t always know why I do what I do"
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3>
/caption = "When I get angry I say things without really knowing why I am saying them"
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4>
/caption = "When I get angry I say things that I later regret "
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5>
/caption = "If I feel insecure I can behave in ways that put others’ backs up "
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6>
/caption = "Sometimes I do things without really knowing why"
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7>
/caption = "I always know what I feel"
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8>
/caption = "Strong feelings often cloud my thinking"
/ options = (" 1 ~nStrongly~ndisagree", " 2 ", " 3 ", " 4 ", " 5 ", " 6 ", " 7 ~nStrongly~nagree")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5", "6", "7")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage rfq8_1>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q1, q2, q3]
</surveypage>

<surveypage rfq8_2>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q4, q5, q6]
</surveypage>

<surveypage rfq8_3>
/ caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ questions = [1 = q7, q8]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey rfq8>
/pages = [
	1 = rfq8_1;
	2 = rfq8_2;
	3 = rfq8_3;
]
/screencapture = false
/ onblockend = [
	expressions.recoding_RFQ_c;
	expressions.recoding_RFQ_u;
]
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 1.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = true
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ finishlabel = "Finish"
</survey>

*******************************************************************************************************************
												End of File
*******************************************************************************************************************